race.comment: TEYLU (1) went close on the Wagga Riverside first-up as favourite and the money came again here following and he was beaten 1.2L in stronger class. The 2kg claim offsets the weight increase and fitter again he deserves another chance. NOCTUA (8) resumed improved when just beaten here first-up. She can use the inside gate to her advantage and has some weight relief at this level with a 1.5kg claim atop. Strips fitter and can improve into the finish. SHE'S HIGH SOCIETY (6) won that contest quickly back on track. Keeps the 1.5kg claim and maps well. Can go back-to-back without surprise. TALIHINA SKY (3) went close as favourite at Orange first-up and has plenty up the sleeve. Has a 3kg claimer aboard and that brings her into it.
